The paper discusses a strategy of sparse approximation, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on evaluating the performance of different methods for selecting a small combination of basis vectors from an overcomplete basis, which is a problem that is relevant to all of these sub-categories.
